{
  "text": "The class of auctions cleared by (2) is very general and suitable for mechanisms with multiple stages of decisions. We will see, in fact, how the two-stages Swiss clearing model described in [CITATION_1] can be abstracted as in (2). But first, we start considering simpler auctions, characterized by single-stage decisions. More specifically, energy procurement auctions where the TSO has to procure a fixed amount of M MW, subject to conditional offer constraints. Hence, we consider auctions cleared by:",
